        <!-- About Cyber Fraud Section -->
        <section id="about" class="section container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>What is Cyber Fraud?</h2>
                <p>Cyber frauds can target anyone. Here are the most common types explained simply.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-md-2 grid-cols-lg-4">
                <div class="about-card glass-card reveal">
                    <div>
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z" /></svg>
                        <h3>Phishing</h3>
                        <p>Fake emails or messages disguised as real ones to steal your passwords, bank details, or personal information.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button class="ai-button" data-scam="Phishing" data-explanation="Imagine a stranger sending you a letter that looks exactly like it's from your bank. The letter asks for your house keys to 'verify your address'. Phishing is the online version of this trick. Scammers send fake emails or messages that look real to fool you into giving them your online passwords and bank details.">Explain Simply</button>
                </div>
                <div class="about-card glass-card reveal" style="transition-delay: 100ms;">
                    <div>
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 18h.01M8 21h8a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H8a2 2 0 00-2 2v14a2 2 0 002 2z" /></svg>
                        <h3>Fake OTP Calls</h3>
                        <p>Fraudsters call pretending to be from a bank or company, tricking you into sharing the One-Time Password (OTP).</p>
                    </div>
                    <button class="ai-button" data-scam="Fake OTP Calls" data-explanation="Think of an OTP as a secret, single-use key to a treasure chest (your account). A scammer calls you, pretending to be a bank employee helping you with a problem. They'll ask for that secret key. If you share it, they can immediately open your account and take what's inside. Real banks never ask for your OTP.">Explain Simply</button>
                </div>
                <div class="about-card glass-card reveal" style="transition-delay: 200ms;">
                    <div>
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 9V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2m2 4h10a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm7-5a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" /></svg>
                        <h3>UPI Fraud</h3>
                        <p>Scammers send fake payment requests or use deceptive QR codes to make you authorize payments to them.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button class="ai-button" data-scam="UPI Fraud" data-explanation="This is a clever digital trick. Scammers send you a 'Collect Money' request on your UPI app, often with a message like 'You've won a prize!'. If you get excited and enter your PIN to approve it, you are not receiving money. Instead, you are authorizing a payment from your account to theirs. Always read the UPI screen carefully before entering your PIN.">Explain Simply</button>
                </div>
                <div class="about-card glass-card reveal" style="transition-delay: 300ms;">
                    <div>
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v9a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2V8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-5m-4 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h4a2 2 0 012 2v1m-4 0h4" /></svg>
                        <h3>Identity Theft</h3>
                        <p>Using your stolen personal data (Aadhaar, PAN) to open bank accounts, take loans, or commit other crimes in your name.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button class="ai-button" data-scam="Identity Theft" data-explanation="This is like someone stealing your wallet, but online. A thief gets a copy of your personal documents, like your Aadhaar or PAN card. They then use this information to pretend to be you. They can open new bank accounts, get credit cards, or take out loans in your name, leaving you with the bill and a damaged reputation.">Explain Simply</button>
